data.text:
Prime has returned from its programming break, and so has WTF Primetime. Vangelus summons Aaron and Omegus to join him as he travels abroad alongside his american compadre Krin. Together, they get their Hurt on.

iTunes users - You can subscribe to and review the podcast here:

iTunes Store

Zune users - You can subscribe here:

zune://subscribe/?WTF@TFW=http://www.tfw2005.com/boards/external.php?type=rss2&forumids=404

The RSS feed which includes a media link for the m4a file is:

WTF @ TFW Transformers Podcast - TFW2005.com

And if you want an MP3 version, it's linked below:

http://www.tfw2005.net/podcast/WTF_Primetime_-_36_-_Hurt_-_August_30_2012.mp3

Never thought I'd see Omegus on a PrimeTime again

EDIT: And after listening to this, I feel the need to say here that I'm most certainly wrong about the new Autobot, even if it does leave some things to be explained

Did Gog say he was gonna say something about the fandom in this episode? Can't wait to listen to that.

EDIT: Never mind he's not in this ep

Seriously. You guys noticed "The one they call" before Megatron's favorite: "*Insert name*, you would be wise to remember, ...!"

Also, Hey Vangelus, you skipped my listener question!

I'd just like to note that the OPENING LINE of "Out of the Past" is Starscream sneering "They said... the one called Arcee is too quick!"

And I had to pause Darkprime's encode while I was laughing my head off.

I have to say it was nice to hear a female on the show, You guys should do that more.

You know, up until this episode of Primetime, I'd forgotten how much I hated the name Hardshell, but now its gonna take me like another month to get over it again haha.

Also, I too liked hearing Crin.

While I approve of the episode in general, I'm so over Miko's character from the first season and a half, that I just didn't care.

Does that make me a bad person? : /
